previewPlan.name: Special Focus Upper Body Level 2
previewPlan.description:
#### **Special Focus: Upper Body Level 2**

This six week training plan is specifically designed to improve your upper body strength and mobility that is often overlooked in endurance athletes. If you are currently in an off-season build or a mid-season bump, with three short focused sessions per week, this plan is ideal.  The combination of strength and yoga sessions will target your shoulders, chest, arms, upper back, and core muscles to help you become a well rounded athlete.

​

Level 2 is ideal if you have recently completed Level 1 or are returning from a three to six month lay-off. As with any of the SYSTM strength plans, take your time with each session and follow the proper progression to experience results.

​

This plan may be applied in conjunction with other Special Focused strength plans, such as Dynamic Focus or combined with one of the 12 week strength add-ons. However, If you choose to apply concurrent plans we suggest that you do so during the off-season or at a time when your endurance training volume is low.

​

The Special Focus stand alone plans follow a 2:1 progression and have three sessions per week on Monday, Wednesday and Friday.

​

Time to rock!
previewPlan.planDescription: This plan is designed to target upper body strength and mobility.

prospects.name: Upper Body Focus 01
prospects.description:
_The primary goal of this series is to increase strength in the major muscles of the chest, back, shoulders and arms. We’ll also focus on improving mobility, stability, and flexibility in the upper body. So get ready for great body-weight-based routines that focus on quality repetitions, endurance holds, and range of motion challenges._

​

As the first session in this series, we’re going to introduce you to some basic upper body movements. This sequence will be beneficial for endurance sports where you need some upper body strength and improved posture, such as swimming, cycling (especially MTB and Cyclocross), and running. To help ensure overall strength, this routine incorporates some core muscle exercises and you may find some portions of the sequence difficult. No problem! Take your time to understand the movement. Pause the video if you need to and embrace the process of mastering new exercises.

​

Unsure if this is the correct strength level for you?  [Click here for help.](https://wahoosystm.com/HelpCenterChooseStrengthLevel)

​

**Exercises Included:**

- Overhead Shoulder Rolls
- Standing T-Spine Rotations
- Lat Press with a Hold
- Hip Hinges on the Wall
- 45 Degree Reverse Fly
- Wide Pushups
- Quadruped Pull-In with Hold
- Quadruped Push-Out with Hold
- Low Plank with Scapular Presses
- Low Side Plank with Toe Taps
- High Plank with Alternate Arm Raise
- Back Extensions
- Cervical Extensions
- Chin Tucks from a Quadruped Position
- Quadruped T-Spine Rotations
- Oblique Leg Lifts
- Side-Lying T-Spine Arcs

prospects.name: Shoulder & Upper Back Mobility A
prospects.description:
This session is designed to improve motion through your shoulders and upper back as well as activate muscles that are key for upper body stability and posture. Take your time to work through the movements and focus on quality range of motion. Do not move into pain. If you have tingling or numbness from any of these movements stop and consult a medical professional. Be sure to rotate through the other routines in this series on a regular basis for maximum benefit.

​

Exercises:

- Forward Shoulder Rolls
- Backward Shoulder Rolls
- Standing T-Spine Rotation
- Standing Scapular Retraction
- Wall Angels
- Scapular Depression
- Quadruped w/Alt. Arm Raise
- Quadruped w/Push Out
- Quadruped w/Pull In
- Downward Dog
